[31m-## Why Dawson uses `<symbol>` (not `<g>`, not raw paths)[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why Dawson Uses `<symbol>`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDawson exports glyphs as `<symbol>` elements intentionally.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis is architectural.[m
 [m
[31m-Dawson exports glyphs as `<symbol>` elements on purpose. This is architectural.[m
[32m+[m[32m### 1) `<symbol>` Is a Viewport[m
 [m
[31m-### 1) `<symbol>` is a viewport ‚Äî `<g>` is not[m
[31m-`<symbol>` supports a `viewBox`.  [m
[31m-`<g>` inherits whatever coordinate system it‚Äôs placed into.[m
[32m+[m[32m`<symbol>` supports its own `viewBox`.[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m`<g>` does not.[m
 [m
[31m-Deterministic exports require each glyph to carry its own:[m
[31m-- origin behavior[m
[31m-- bounds[m
[31m-- padding policy[m
[31m-- scaling semantics when instanced[m
[32m+[m[32mEach glyph must define:[m
 [m
[31m-That requires a per-glyph viewport ‚Üí `<symbol>`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- its own coordinate system[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- its own bounds[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- its own origin[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- its own scaling behavior[m[41m  [m
 [m
[31m-### 2) `<symbol>` + `<use>` = instanceable geometry[m
[31m-The whole point is reuse:[m
[32m+[m[32mDeterministic geometry requires per-glyph viewports.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2) `<symbol>` + `<use>` = Clean Instancing[m
 [m
 ```html[m
[31m-<use href="#glyph-id" width="..." height="..." />[m
\ No newline at end of file[m
[32m+[m[32m<use href="#glyph-id" width="..." height="..." />[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis provides:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- no geometry duplication[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- no runtime transforms[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- centralized definitions[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- reduced DOM weight[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 3) Encapsulation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBaseline alignment, SAFE padding, and DECK centering are baked into geometry.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`<symbol>` keeps each glyph self-contained so it behaves the same in every environment.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 4) Wrapper Flexibility[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe geometry is fully baked.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf needed, `<symbol>` can be converted to:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- `<g id="...">`[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- `<path id="...">`[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- inline geometry[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- React components[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- CAD ingestion[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- game engine ingestion[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe coordinates do not change.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## SAFE Padding ‚Äî Why 6 Units[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBecause 2 units is mathematically sufficient but operationally fragile.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mMost fonts use UPM = 2048.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAt 100px render:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- 2 units ‚âà 0.1px (below rounding noise)[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- 6 units remains visually negligible but survives real rendering environments[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m6 units:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- survives subpixel rounding[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- prevents edge clipping[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- tolerates stroke expansion[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- holds up under scaling[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPadding does not change glyph proportions or advance width.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIt prevents support problems.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Baseline Normalization[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRaw font exports assume a typesetting engine will calculate baseline alignment.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNaive exports introduce:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- conditional Y-offset logic[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- runtime baseline detection[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- mixed-case alignment math[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- increased error surface[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDawson bakes baseline alignment into geometry during export.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mResult:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- no runtime baseline math[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- no conditional logic[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- mixed-case alignment works immediately[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mLowercase letterforms are not modified.[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32mOnly coordinate space is normalized.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Strokes and ViewBox Clipping[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mStroking `<use>` references is inconsistent across renderers.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf stroke is required, apply it to the `<path>` inside the `<symbol>` using CSS variables.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mImportant:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mA stroke expands outward from geometry.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRequired padding ‚â• stroke_width / 2[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf heavy strokes are needed, export with a larger SAFE padding target.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDefault exports optimize deterministic fill geometry, not arbitrary outline expansion.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
